HEADWORD: Insatiable
<hw>In*sa"tia*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>insatiable</ets>, L. <ets>ionsatiabilis</ets>. See <er>In-</er>
not, and <er>Satiable</er>.]</ety> <def>Not satiable; incapable of being
satisfied or appeased; very greedy; <as>as, an <ex>insatiable</ex>
appetite, thirst, or desire</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>⟦ldquo⟧<qex>Insatiable</qex> of glory.⟦rdquo⟧</q>
